## 2. System Architecture

### High-Level Architecture

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                   CLIENT (Browser)                │
│   React SPA · Vite · Port 5173/5174              │
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│   AuthContext  ←→  localStorage (token, user)     │
│   api.js       →   Axios with interceptors        │
│   React Router →   Public + Private + Admin routes│
└──────────────┬───────────────────────────────────┘
               │ HTTP (REST JSON)
               ▼
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              API SERVER (Express.js)              │
│   Port 5000 · Node.js                            │
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│   Middleware Stack:                               │
│   helmet → mongoSanitize → cors → json → routes  │
│                                                   │
│   Rate Limiting:                                  │
│   Auth routes: 15 req / 15 min                   │
│   General:     100 req / 15 min                  │
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│   Routes → Controllers → Models → MongoDB        │
└──────────────┬───────────────────────────────────┘
               │ Mongoose Driver
               ▼
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│           MongoDB Atlas (Cloud)                   │
│   Collections: users, admins, campaigns,          │
│   donations, contacts, payments, tokens          │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Authentication Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User Browser
    participant F as React Frontend
    participant B as Express Backend
    participant DB as MongoDB

    U->>F: Fill login form
    F->>B: POST /api/auth/login {email, password}
    B->>DB: User.findOne({email})
    DB-->>B: User document
    B->>B: bcrypt.compare(password, hash)
    B->>B: jwt.sign({id}, SECRET, {expiresIn: '7d'})
    B-->>F: {token, user: {id, name, email}}
    F->>F: AuthContext.login(token, user)
    F->>F: localStorage.setItem('token', token)
    F-->>U: Redirect to /dashboard
```

### Password Reset Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant F as Frontend
    participant B as Backend
    participant E as Email (Nodemailer)
    participant DB as MongoDB

    U->>F: Click "Forgot Password"
    F->>B: POST /api/auth/forgot-password {email}
    B->>DB: Find user by email
    B->>B: Generate crypto.randomBytes(32)
    B->>B: SHA-256 hash the token
    B->>DB: Save hashed token (1hr TTL)
    B->>E: Send email with reset URL
    E-->>U: Email with reset link
    U->>F: Click link → /reset-password/:userId/:token
    F->>B: POST /api/auth/reset-password/:userId/:token {password}
    B->>B: SHA-256 hash incoming token
    B->>DB: Find matching token doc
    B->>DB: Update user password (pre-save hook hashes it)
    B->>DB: Delete used token
    B-->>F: Success
    F-->>U: Redirect to login
```

